   "source": [
    "# Quick Start: Basic 3D Tissue Reconstruction\n",
    "\n",space_map
    "This notebook demonstrates the basic workflow for reconstructing 3D tissue maps from serial section data using Space-map.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "Space-map uses a two-stage registration approach:\n",
    "1. **Coarse Alignment**: Affine transformation for global positioning\n",
    "2. **Fine Alignment**: LDDMM (Large Deformation Diffeomorphic Metric Mapping) for local deformations\n",
    "\n",
    "## Prerequisites\n",
    "\n",
    "Make sure you have Space-map installed:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "pip install spacemap\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Import Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import spacemap\n",
    "from spacemap import Slice\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Space-map version: {spacemap.__version__}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Load Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Load cell coordinate data from a CSV file. The data should contain:\n",
    "- `x`, `y`: Cell coordinates\n",
    "- `layer`: Section/slice identifier"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load data (replace with your data path)\n",
    "# For this example, we'll create synthetic data\n",
    "# In real use, you would load from: df = pd.read_csv(\"path/to/cells.csv.gz\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create synthetic data for demonstration\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "n_layers = 5\n",
    "n_cells_per_layer = 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate data with some structure\n",
    "data_list = []\n",
    "for layer_id in range(n_layers):\n",
    "    # Create clusters of cells\n",
    "    n_clusters = 3\n",
    "    for cluster in range(n_clusters):\n",
    "        center_x = np.random.uniform(100, 900)\n",
    "        center_y = np.random.uniform(100, 900)\n",
    "        n_cells = n_cells_per_layer // n_clusters\n",
    "        \n",
    "        x = np.random.normal(center_x, 50, n_cells)\n",
    "        y = np.random.normal(center_y, 50, n_cells)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Add slight rotation and shift per layer to simulate tissue sections\n",
    "        angle = layer_id * 0.05\n",
    "        x_rot = x * np.cos(angle) - y * np.sin(angle)\n",
    "        y_rot = x * np.sin(angle) + y * np.cos(angle)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        layer_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "            'x': x_rot + layer_id * 5,\n",
    "            'y': y_rot + layer_id * 5,\n",
    "            'layer': layer_id\n",
    "        })\n",
    "        data_list.append(layer_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.concat(data_list, ignore_index=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(df)} cells across {df['layer'].nunique()} layers\")\n",
    "print(f\"Layer distribution:\\n{df['layer'].value_counts().sort_index()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Organize Data by Layers\n",
    "\n",
    "Extract coordinates for each layer and prepare for registration."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Group by layer and extract coordinates\n",
    "xys = []\n",
    "layer_ids = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for layer_id in sorted(df['layer'].unique()):\n",
    "    layer_data = df[df['layer'] == layer_id]\n",
    "    xy = layer_data[['x', 'y']].values\n",
    "    xys.append(xy)\n",
    "    layer_ids.append(layer_id)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Prepared {len(xys)} layers for registration\")\n",
    "for i, (layer_id, xy) in enumerate(zip(layer_ids, xys)):\n",
    "    print(f\"  Layer {layer_id}: {xy.shape[0]} cells\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Initialize Space-map Project\n",
    "\n",
    "Create a project directory and initialize the flow processing system."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set up project base directory\n",
    "BASE = \"data/quickstart_demo\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize the flow import system\n",
    "flowImport = spacemap.flow.FlowImport(BASE)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize slices with cell coordinates\n",
    "flowImport.init_xys(xys, ids=layer_ids)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get slice objects for processing\n",
    "slices = flowImport.slices\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Initialized {len(slices)} slices\")\n",
    "print(f\"XY Range: {spacemap.XYRANGE}\")\n",
    "print(f\"XYD: {spacemap.XYD}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Perform Affine Registration (Coarse Alignment)\n",
    "\n",
    "Apply affine transformations to align adjacent sections globally."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create registration manager\n",
    "mgr = spacemap.flow.AutoFlowMultiCenter4(slices, Slice.rawKey)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set alignment method (options: \"sift\", \"sift_vgg\", \"auto\")\n",
    "mgr.alignMethod = \"auto\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Perform affine registration\n",
    "# \"DF\" indicates using density field representation\n",
    "# show=True displays intermediate results (set to False for faster processing)\n",
    "mgr.affine(\"DF\", show=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Affine registration completed!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 6: Perform LDDMM Registration (Fine Alignment)\n",
    "\n",
    "Apply large deformation diffeomorphic metric mapping for precise local alignment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Perform LDDMM registration\n",
    "# This aligns slices using non-rigid deformation while preserving topology\n",
    "mgr.ldm_pair(Slice.align1Key, Slice.align2Key, show=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"LDDMM registration completed!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 7: Visualize Results\n",
    "\n",
    "Create 2D and 3D visualizations of the aligned tissue sections."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualize aligned sections in 2D (overlay)\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, len(slices)-1, figsize=(20, 4))\n",
    "if len(slices) == 2:\n",
    "    axes = [axes]\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(len(slices) - 1):\n",
    "    # Get aligned coordinates\n",
    "    points1 = slices[i].imgs[Slice.rawKey].get_points(Slice.align2Key)\n",
    "    points2 = slices[i+1].imgs[Slice.rawKey].get_points(Slice.align2Key)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Plot\n",
    "    axes[i].scatter(points1[:, 0], points1[:, 1], s=1, alpha=0.5, c='red', label=f'Layer {i}')\n",
    "    axes[i].scatter(points2[:, 0], points2[:, 1], s=1, alpha=0.5, c='blue', label=f'Layer {i+1}')\n",
    "    axes[i].set_title(f'Layers {i} & {i+1}')\n",
    "    axes[i].legend()\n",
    "    axes[i].axis('equal')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(f'{BASE}/alignment_2d.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"2D visualization saved!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create 3D visualization\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use different colors for each layer\n",
    "colors = plt.cm.viridis(np.linspace(0, 1, len(slices)))\n",
    "\n",
    "z_spacing = 10  # Units spacing between layers\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, slice_obj in enumerate(slices):\n",
    "    # Get aligned coordinates\n",
    "    points = slice_obj.imgs[Slice.rawKey].get_points(Slice.align2Key)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Add z-coordinate\n",
    "    z = np.ones(len(points)) * i * z_spacing\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Plot\n",
    "    ax.scatter(points[:, 0], points[:, 1], z, \n",
    "               c=[colors[i]], s=1, alpha=0.6, label=f'Layer {i}')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('X')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Y')\n",
    "ax.set_zlabel('Z (Layer)')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.set_title('3D Tissue Reconstruction')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.savefig(f'{BASE}/reconstruction_3d.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"3D visualization saved!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 8: Export Results\n",
    "\n",
    "Export aligned coordinates and 3D model for further analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create export manager\n",
    "export = spacemap.flow.FlowExport(slices)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Collect all aligned points into a single dataset\n",
    "all_points = []\n",
    "all_layers = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, slice_obj in enumerate(slices):\n",
    "    points = slice_obj.imgs[Slice.rawKey].get_points(Slice.align2Key)\n",
    "    z = np.ones(len(points)) * i * z_spacing\n",
    "    points_3d = np.column_stack([points, z])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    all_points.append(points_3d)\n",
    "    all_layers.extend([i] * len(points))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Combine all points\n",
    "model_3d = np.vstack(all_points)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save as CSV\n",
    "output_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'x': model_3d[:, 0],\n",
    "    'y': model_3d[:, 1],\n",
    "    'z': model_3d[:, 2],\n",
    "    'layer': all_layers\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "output_df.to_csv(f'{BASE}/aligned_cells_3d.csv.gz', index=False, compression='gzip')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save as numpy array\n",
    "np.save(f'{BASE}/model_3d.npy', model_3d)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Results exported to {BASE}/\")\n",
    "print(f\"  - aligned_cells_3d.csv.gz: {len(output_df)} cells\")\n",
    "print(f\"  - model_3d.npy: {model_3d.shape} array\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "In this quickstart, we:\n",
    "1. Loaded cell coordinate data from multiple tissue sections\n",
    "2. Initialized a Space-map project\n",
    "3. Performed two-stage registration (affine + LDDMM)\n",
    "4. Visualized the aligned sections in 2D and 3D\n",
    "5. Exported the results for further analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "## Next Steps\n",
    "\n",
    "- See `02_advanced_registration.ipynb` for advanced registration options\n",
    "- See `03_image_features.ipynb` for using histology images\n",
    "- Check the [documentation](https://a12910.github.io/space-map) for detailed API reference"
   ]
  }
